[SECURITY] TOTP verification failed

Someone authenticated with a valid password but failed the TOTP
challenge. One occurrence is usually a typo or a stale clock; repeated
ones from new IPs are an attack signal.

  Event  : {{ event_type }}
  When   : {{ when_str }}
  IP     : {{ ip or '(unknown)' }}
  Agent  : {{ user_agent or '(none)' }}
  Reason : {{ extra or '(none)' }}

Implications: the password is known to the requester. If this IP is
not yours, treat the password as compromised.

What to do:
  1. If the IP is unfamiliar, rotate the admin password immediately.
  2. Look at auth_events for bursts of login_mfa_failed from one IP.
  3. From a familiar IP, no action — replay guard handled it.
